cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper analyzes the relationship between bibliographic characteristics of scientific documents and citation and Mendeley readership counts, which falls under the scope of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the analysis is based on a large-scale dataset of publications from different fields covered by the Web of Science, it is difficult to narrow down to a specific sub-category.
